1
Who Decides Why and How We Process Your Personal Information
We determine why and how we process your personal information and we are responsible for your personal data. For residents in the EU, we are the data processor of your personal information when you use our services.
2
How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
We collect your personal information primarily to make it easier and more satisfying for you to use our services, and the information you provide helps us achieve this goal.
You understand and agree that we hope to provide perfect products and services. Therefore, we will continue to improve our products and services, which means that with their iteration, expansion and upgrade, we may launch new services or business functions, or re-arrange business functions, and may require the collection of new types of personal information or change the purpose or method of processing personal information.
(a)
What types of personal information do we collect from or about you
Personal information refers to all kinds of information related to identified or identifiable natural persons recorded by electronic or other means, excluding the information processed anonymously. The meaning of personal information may differ in different jurisdictions according to applicable laws and regulations.
NETSTORY collects information about you as described below. As set out below in more details, we use and in specific cases combine that information to operate, tailor content, personalize and adjust and improve our services, and to send you messages or personalized information about new features and more, including for marketing and promotional purposes in accordance with your preferences.
(i) Create an account and log in
(ii)
