6
How We Protect Personal Information of Children
We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from a child under the age of 14 (or the age of majority in your jurisdiction of residence), nor do we knowingly allow children to use our service. If you are a child under 14 (or the age of majority in your jurisdiction of residence), please do not send any information about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, email address or other personal information. No one under the age of 14 may provide any personal information. If you believe that we have collected personal information from a child, please contact us using the contact details as set forth below. In the event that we learn that we have collected personal information from a child, we will delete that information as soon as commercially practicable.
7
International Transfers
We may transfer information that we collect about you to other third parties cross borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world. Please note that these countries and jurisdictions may not have the same data protection laws as your own jurisdiction, and we take steps to ensure adequate safeguards are in place to enable the transfer of information and the use and disclosure of information about you, including personal information, as described in this Policy.
8
How to Manage Your Personal Information
(a)
Your choices about information provided by you
If you do not want to provide NETSTORY with personal information, then you can choose not to provide it. If you choose not to provide us with personal information, we may not always be able to provide you with our services you want. For example, without providing an email address, you cannot create an account to pay for our services.
(b)
Your choices about information provided by third parties
You may be able to control how third parties collect and share your information by changing your preferences or opting out of collection directly with those third parties. Before disclosing information to third parties, we recommend you check their respective privacy policies for further details.
(c)
Your marketing and advertising choices
You can exercise choices over how we use your personal information and update your preferences at any time:
·
To remove yourself from individual contests or promotions, or to opt-out from receiving marketing communications from us, simply contact us using the details set out in “How to Contact Us”. If you opt-out of receiving email marketing communications from us, please note we may still contact you occasionally about the status of your account, such as to inform you that your account may be expiring, or for other service related information.
·
To disable selected tracking technologies from collecting information relating to the effectiveness of advertising campaigns or analytics data and from serving you with personalized advertising on our services, please refer to guidance provided by your device manufacturer, operating system developer, or individual web browser if you would like help in managing your preferences with respect to tracking technologies used on our services.
(d)
Accessing and deleting your information
You may deactivate your NETSTORY account or delete email associated with your account by contacting us using the details set out in “How to Contact Us”.
If you would like to access or view the personal information we hold about you or for any reason you are concerned with the way we are using your personal information, or would like to correct or request that we delete such personal information, you can also contact us using the details set out in “How to Contact Us”.
If you are a California resident or a user in the European Economic Area (“EEA”), UK or Switzerland and would like to know more about your rights in connection with your personal information, please see the relevant appendices sections below.
9
Notices and Amendments
We may update this Policy from time to time to reflect changes to our information practices. If we make any material changes we will notify you by email (sent to the email address specified in your account) or by means of a notice on our services prior to the change becoming effective. If we are required by applicable data protection laws and regulations to give you enhanced notice or seek your consent to any such changes, we will do so. You can see when this Policy was last updated by checking the "last updated" date displayed at the top of this Policy. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices.
